1 (c) Except as otherwise provided in paragraphs (e), (f), and (g) of this
2 subsection, if a party appeals an order ruling on a motion pursuant to
3 subsection (4) of this section, all proceedings between all parties in
4 the action shall be stayed. The stay shall remain in effect until the
5 conclusion of the appeal.
6 (d) During a stay issued pursuant to paragraph (a) of this subsection,
7 the court may allow limited discovery if a party shows that specific
8 information is necessary to establish whether a party has satisfied or
9 failed to satisfy a burden pursuant to subsection (8) of this section
10 and the information is not reasonably available unless discovery is
11 allowed.
12 (e) A motion pursuant to subsection (11) of this section for costs, at-
13 torney's fees, and expenses shall not be subject to a stay pursuant to
14 this subsection.
15 (f) A stay issued pursuant to the provisions of this subsection shall
16 not affect a party's ability to voluntarily dismiss a cause of action or
17 part of a cause of action.
18 (g) During a stay issued pursuant to the provisions of this subsection,
19 the court for good cause may hear and rule on a motion unrelated to the
20 motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this section.
21 (6)(a) The court shall hear a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this
22 section no later than sixty (60) days after filing of the motion, unless
23 the court orders a later hearing:
24 (i) To allow discovery pursuant to subsection (5)(d) of this sec-
25 tion; or
26 (ii) For other good cause.
27 (b) If the court orders a later hearing pursuant to paragraph (a) of
28 this subsection, the court shall hear the motion pursuant to subsection
29 (5) of this section no later than sixty (60) days after the court or-
30 der allowing the discovery, unless the court orders a later hearing pur-
31 suant to paragraph (a)(ii) of this subsection.
32 (7) In ruling on a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this section,
33 the court shall consider the pleadings, the motion, any reply or response to
34 the motion, and any evidence that could be considered in ruling on a motion
35 for summary judgment pursuant to applicable court rule.
36 (8)(a) In ruling on a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this section,
37 the court shall dismiss with prejudice a cause of action or part of a
38 cause of action if:
39 (i) The responding party fails to establish a prima facie case as
40 to each essential element of the cause of action; or
41 (ii) The moving party establishes that:
42 1. The responding party failed to state a cause of action
43 upon which relief can be granted; or
44 2. There is no genuine issue as to any material fact and the
45 moving party is entitled to judgment as a matter of law on the
46 cause of action or part of the cause of action.
47 (b) A voluntary dismissal with or without prejudice of a responding
48 party's cause of action or part of a cause of action that is the subject
49 of a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this section shall not affect a
50 moving party's right to obtain a ruling on the motion and to seek costs,

