1 attorney's fees, and expenses pursuant to subsection (11) of this sec-
2 tion.
3 (9) The court shall rule on a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this
4 section no later than sixty (60) days after a hearing held pursuant to sub-
5 section (6) of this section.
6 (10) A moving party may appeal as a matter of right from an order deny-
7 ing, in whole or in part, a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this section.
8 The appeal shall be filed within forty-two (42) days after entry of the order
9 pursuant to applicable court rule.
10 (11) Upon a motion pursuant to subsection (4) of this section, the court
11 shall award court costs, reasonable attorney's fees, and reasonable litiga-
12 tion expenses related to the motion to the prevailing party.
13 (3) (12) Notwithstanding Except as provided in subsection (11) of this
14 section and notwithstanding any other provision of law, including chapter
15 1, title 12, Idaho Code, a court may not award costs or attorney's fees to a
16 defendant in an action brought under this section unless the defendant has
17 complied with the applicable requirements of sections 18-8803 and 18-8804,
18 Idaho Code court finds that the defendant has complied with the defense of
19 life act, as contained in section 18-622, Idaho Code.
20 (4) (13) The civil causes of action provided for in this section exist
21 independently of any criminal action commenced pursuant to this chapter. A
22 civil cause of action may be pursued under the provisions of this chapter
23 even if a criminal prosecution is not pursued.
24 (5) (14) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, including chap-
25 ters 14, 17, and 18, title 54, Idaho Code, the requirements of this section
26 shall be enforced exclusively through the private civil causes of action
27 described. No enforcement of this section may be taken or threatened against
28 any person by this state, a political subdivision of this state, a prosecut-
29 ing attorney, or an executive or administrative officer or employee of this
30 state or a political subdivision of this state.
31 (6) (15) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, this state, a state
32 official, or a prosecuting attorney may not intervene in an action brought
33 under this section. Nothing in this subsection shall prohibit a person de-
34 scribed in this subsection from filing an amicus curiae brief in the action.
35 (7) (16) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect any familial
36 rights or responsibilities or any proceedings conducted under Idaho law.
37 (8) (17) In an action brought under this section, a court may not award
38 compensatory or punitive damages if a person demonstrates that the person
39 paid, or has been ordered to pay, compensatory or punitive damages, respec-
40 tively, in a previous civil action for that particular violation of this
41 chapter.
42 (9) (18) Notwithstanding any other law to the contrary, a civil action
43 may not be brought under this section by a person who, through an act of rape,
44 sexual assault, incest, or other criminal conduct, impregnated the pregnant
45 woman seeking an abortion in violation of this chapter.
46 (10) (19) Notwithstanding any other law to the contrary, the following
47 shall not be defenses to an action brought under this section:
48 (a) That the pregnant woman or, if the pregnant woman is a minor, a par-
49 ent or guardian consented to an unlawful abortion;
50 (b) Ignorance or mistake of law;

