10 (11) (20) Notwithstanding Except as provided in subsection (11) of this
11 section and notwithstanding any other law to the contrary, a court may:
12 (a) Not award attorney's fees or costs to a person subject to an ac-
13 tion brought under this section, unless the action is frivolous, with-
14 out foundation, or brought in bad faith or for the sole reason for delay;
15 (b) Not award attorney's fees or costs to a person who prevails in
16 challenging the constitutionality of this section under state law, un-
17 less the defense of this section is frivolous, without foundation, or
18 brought in bad faith or for the sole reason for delay; and
19 (c) Award attorney's fees or costs to a person who prevails in defending
20 the constitutionality of this section under state law, even though the
21 challenge to the constitutionality of this section was not frivolous,
22 without foundation, or brought in bad faith or for the sole reason for
23 delay.
24 (12) (21) The provisions of this section shall not be construed to im-
25 pose liability on speech or conduct protected by the first amendment of the
26 United States constitution or by section 9, article I of the constitution of
27 the state of Idaho.
28 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
29 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
30 July 1, 2025.

